## Interaction Contract

- `modelValue` is treated as the source of truth; every add/remove emits both `update:modelValue` and `change` with a new array.
- Input text is trimmed before insertion. Empty tags are ignored.
- Duplicate suppression is exact after trimming unless `allowDuplicates=true`.
- `separators` split pasted or typed input; Enter always confirms the current input.
- When `confirmOnBlur=true`, blur commits unfinished input after emitting the native blur event.
- Backspace removes the last tag only when the input is empty.
- `disabled` prevents adding/removing tags and disables existing chip close actions.
- Reaching `max` disables the inner input and clears the placeholder.

## API

### TxTagInput Props

| Name | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|------|------|
| `modelValue` | `string[]` | `[]` | Tag list |
| `placeholder` | `string` | `'Add tag'` | Placeholder text |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disabled state |
| `max` | `number` | `20` | Max tag count |
| `allowDuplicates` | `boolean` | `false` | Allow duplicate tags |
| `separators` | `string[]` | `[',']` | Separator characters |
| `confirmOnBlur` | `boolean` | `true` | Confirm on blur |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|------|------|
| `update:modelValue` | `(tags: string[])` | Emitted with the next complete tag list. |
| `change` | `(tags: string[])` | Emitted with the same next list after add/remove. |
| `add` | `(tags: string[])` | Emitted with tags accepted by the current operation. |
| `remove` | `(tag: string)` | Emitted with the removed tag value. |
| `focus` | `(event: FocusEvent)` | Forwarded native input focus event. |
| `blur` | `(event: FocusEvent)` | Forwarded native input blur event; may commit unfinished input when `confirmOnBlur=true`. |

### Slots

`TxTagInput` does not expose custom slots. Existing tags are rendered with `TxTag`; compose labels, help text, or validation messages outside the component.

## Best Practices

- Keep tags short and searchable. Release notes, approval reasons, and long descriptions belong in text fields or detail forms.
- Set `max` to the smallest useful limit for the workflow; when the limit is reached the inner input is disabled and the placeholder disappears.
- Keep `allowDuplicates` off unless duplicate labels are meaningful in the same collection. Duplicate suppression is exact after trimming, not case-insensitive.
- Add every delimiter you show in help text to `separators`; Enter always confirms the current input, and `confirmOnBlur` controls whether unfinished input is committed on blur.

